Both the experimental and modeling result suggests that Stokes shift is not ultimately a useful design parameter to identify how well a luminophore will perform in LSCs over large area. Here we define a new parameter, the overlap integral (OI) to quantify the reabsorption properties of a luminophore as:3OI=∫0∞A(λ)·PL⁎(λ)dλ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
